This paper discusses the LOCKSS digital preservation system, which is primarily concerned with preserving and migrating web content. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries). The paper also touches on issues related to security and information retrieval, which could place it in categories such as cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper discusses the technical implementation of the format migration process, which could place it in categories such as cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
